<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4524] .NET Core Server doesn&apos;t close properly when cancelled</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4524</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;My code starts a server with a cancellation token and then later stops it&#160;by triggering the token.&#160; When it does, the server fails to close cleanly and my code cannot then start another server on the same port.&#160; The problem is that the Task which is responsible for opening and closing the connection in AsyncBaseServer throws a TokenCancelationException in the Task.Delay call which is not caught and therefore bombs out the task without closing the socket.&#160; I will raise a pull request with a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 10 Surface Pro 4. Xamarin.Forms app.&#160; .NET Standard 2.0 libraries.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
